'''Crew-served weapon'''
# '''Military Term''' (''notably [[w:USMC|USMC]]''). A weapon which is too heavy for one man to carry, and is as such ''served'' by usually 2-4 men. An example of this would be a heavy [[w:machine gun|machine gun]] or [[w:Rocket launcher|rocket launcher]], such as the [[w:FGM-148 Javelin|FGM-148 Javelin]].